The paper describes a method for detecting active speakers in videos using a 3D CNN and an ensemble of temporal convolution and LSTM classifiers. This involves processing visual and temporal information, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of LSTM classifiers suggests that the paper may also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category. The use of an ensemble of classifiers suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks suggests that the paper may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
